title: Static Analysis

android.permission.USE_FINGERPRINT.description: This constant was deprecated in API level 28. Applications should request USE_BIOMETRIC instead

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH.description: Allows applications to connect to paired bluetooth devices.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_NUMBERS.description: Allows read access to the device's phone number(s). This is a subset of the capabilities granted by

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has full RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In Full RELRO, the entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) is marked as read-only.

rpath.description: The shared object does not have run-time search path or RPATH set.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

metadata.description: Query Database of SMS, Contacts etc

metadata.cwe: CWE-327 Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: MD5 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.

metadata.cwe: CWE-327 Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: SHA-1 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.
The App logs information. Sensitive information should never be logged.
metadata.cwe: CWE-532 Insertion of Sensitive Information into Log File

metadata.description: App can read/write to External Storage. Any App can read data written to External Storage.
App creates temp file. Sensitive information should never be written into a temp file.

metadata.cwe: CWE-312 Cleartext Storage of Sensitive Information
metadata.description: Files may contain hardcoded sensitive informations like usernames, passwords, keys etc.
This App copies data to clipboard. Sensitive data should not be copied to clipboard as other applications can access it.
App uses SQLite Database and execute raw SQL query. Untrusted user input in raw SQL queries can cause SQL Injection. Also sensitive information should be encrypted and written to the database.
metadata.cwe: CWE-89 Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')

metadata.description: Insecure WebView Implementation. Execution of user controlled code in WebView is a critical Security Hole.
metadata.cwe: CWE-749 Exposed Dangerous Method or Function

metadata.description: The App uses an insecure Random Number Generator.
metadata.cwe: CWE-330 Use of Insufficiently Random Values

FCS_RBG_EXT.1.1.choice: The application implement DRBG functionality for its cryptographic operations.

FCS_STO_EXT.1.1.choice: The application does not store any credentials to non-volatile memory.

FCS_CKM_EXT.1.1.choice: The application implement asymmetric key generation.

FDP_DEC_EXT.1.1.choice: The application has access to ['bluetooth', 'camera', 'network connectivity', 'location'].

FDP_DEC_EXT.1.2.choice: The application has access to no sensitive information repositories.

FDP_NET_EXT.1.1.choice: The application has user/application initiated network communications.

FDP_DAR_EXT.1.1.choice: The application implement functionality to encrypt sensitive data in non-volatile memory.

FMT_MEC_EXT.1.1.choice: The application invoke the mechanisms recommended by the platform vendor for storing and setting configuration options.

FTP_DIT_EXT.1.1.choice: The application does encrypt some transmitted data with HTTPS/TLS/SSH between itself and another trusted IT product.

FCS_RBG_EXT.2.1,FCS_RBG_EXT.2.2.choice: The application perform all deterministic random bit generation (DRBG) services in accordance with NIST Special Publication 800-90A using Hash_DRBG. The deterministic RBG is seeded by an entropy source that accumulates entropy from a platform-based DRBG and a software-based noise source, with a minimum of 256 bits of entropy at least equal to the greatest security strength (according to NIST SP 800-57) of the keys and hashes that it will generate.

FCS_CKM.1.1(1).choice: The application generate asymmetric cryptographic keys not in accordance with FCS_CKM.1.1(1) using key generation algorithm RSA schemes and cryptographic key sizes of 1024-bit or lower.

playstore_details.title: DoWallet: Bitcoin Wallet. A Secure Crypto Wallet.
playstore_details.description:
DoWallet: the simple, safe way to buy and manage your cryptocurrency in our easy to use Bitcoin Wallet - the best Bitcoin Wallet. Receive, Send & Buy Bitcoin (BTC), Litecoin (LTC), Ethereum (ETH), and Bitcoin Cash (BCH).
 
Managing your crypto assets has never been easier. DoWallet provides maximum security while keeping simplicity, allowing all types of users to easily manage, transfer & (soon) exchange their currencies. DoWallet allows users to connect to top exchanges like Coinbase, Binance, Kraken and Gemini to have a consolidated dashboard view of their positions.
 
DoWallet Bitcoin Wallet is a powerful and easy to use Bitcoin Wallet & Crypto Wallet that allows users to easily control their own "private keys". You can instantly transact (receive & send Bitcoin, Litecoin, Ethereum and Bitcoin Cash) with anyone in the world and transform the financial system right from your pocket.

Buy Easily
Own crypto in an instant: Buy Bitcoin with debit card, simple and fast.

Buying Bitcoin in an ATM?
No worries. Get your Bitcoin Wallet address in seconds and buy safely in a Bitcoin ATM.
 
Take control of your funds - take control of your Bitcoin! With our Bitcoin Wallet, only YOU have access to your funds or transaction data. Neither DoWallet Bitcoin Wallet or any 3rd party can access your money or data. You get the financial privacy and autonomy that blockchain and cryptocurrency were designed for.

Want to see other cryptos or support exchanges in our Bitcoin Wallet? Send us a request to support@dowallet.app.
 
Highlights of DoWallet Bitcoin & Crypto Wallet:
✓ Secure Bitcoin Wallet & Crypto Wallet. All transactions can be authorized solely by you via PIN and biometric authentication.
✓ Crypto Wallet: send and receive Bitcoin (BTC), Litecoin (LTC), Ethereum (ETH), Bitcoin Cash (BCH) instantly.
✓ Connect your crypto exchanges: View your balances in one easy dashboard across the major crypto exchanges including Coinbase, Poloniex, Bitstamp, Bitfinex, Bittrex, Gemini, Kraken, Binance, HitBTC, etc.  
✓ Buy Bitcoin and/or Buy Ethereum using a debit card.
✓ Multi-Wallet Functionality: Have multiple Bitcoin wallets, Litecoin wallets, Ethereum Wallets and Bitcoin Cash wallets all within the same account. Create a BTC account for business, another for personal use. DoWallet is designed for you to do business how you see fit.
✓ Multi-Account: Users can toggle between multiple DoWallet accounts on the same device using our unique multi-user architecture that preserve privacy across accounts.
✓ Anti-Scam & Anti-Phishing: DoWallet tracks thousands of flagged wallets to prevent users from accidentally sending money to potentially compromised accounts
✓ Transaction history with full transaction details.
✓ Price Charts: Track real time and historical Bitcoin (BTC), Litecoin (LTC), Ethereum (ETH), Bitcoin Cash (BCH)- and many other crypto assets,  prices and market data, with beautifully customized charts.
✓ News: Access aggregated news from the world’s top crypto news sources, organized by currency.
✓ Send & request: easily send and request money from any of your contacts using their phone, email, send and request via QR code or using their Bitcoin Wallet address, Bitcoin Cash Wallet address, Ethereum Wallet address or Litecoin Wallet address.
✓ Zero-knowledge & zero-access to user funds, keys, or transaction data by DoWallet or 3rd parties.
✓ Simple account creation.
✓ Real-time fiat-crypto-fiat currency conversion rates. We support 60 different currencies (fiat).
✓ Simplified backup and recovery with a 12 word backup phrase.
 
Bitcoin Wallet for Android
DoWallet Bitcoin Wallet for Android has been designed from the ground up to to provide the best experience on your Android.
 
No personal info or contact list info ever leaves the device without first being encrypted by the user's credentials. Neither DoWallet nor any 3rd party can access the information requested by the application.
